PostgreSQL WAL Logical Replication Setup with wal2json
## 1. Install PostgreSQL 13
yum module reset postgresql -y
yum module enable postgresql:13 -y
yum install postgresql-server postgresql-devel gcc make -y

## 2. Initialize Database
postgresql-setup --initdb
Error (if directory not empty):
ERROR: Data directory /var/lib/pgsql/data is not empty!

Fix:
systemctl stop postgresql
mv /var/lib/pgsql/data /var/lib/pgsql/data_old
postgresql-setup --initdb

## 3. Start PostgreSQL Service
systemctl enable postgresql --now

## 4. Verify Development Files
find /usr -name pgxs.mk

Expected Output:
/usr/lib64/pgsql/pgxs/src/makefiles/pgxs.mk

##5. Build wal2json

cd /wal2json
make
make install

If Error:

gcc: error: redhat-hardened-cc1: No such file or directory

Fix:
yum install redhat-rpm-config -y
make clean
make
make install

Expected Output:
/usr/bin/install -c -m 755 wal2json.so '/usr/lib64/pgsql/'

## 6. Configure PostgreSQL for Logical Replication

Edit postgresql.conf:

wal_level = logical
max_replication_slots = 5
max_wal_senders = 5

Restart PostgreSQL:

systemctl restart postgresql

## 7. Connect to PostgreSQL
psql -U postgres

If error:

FATAL: Peer authentication failed for user "postgres"

Fix:

su - postgres
psql
## 8. Create Logical Replication Slot
SELECT * FROM pg_create_logical_replication_slot('binlog_slot', 'wal2json');

Expected Output:

 slot_name  |    lsn
------------+-----------
 binlog_slot | 0/XXXXXXXX

## 9. Create Test Table
CREATE TABLE test_log(id INT, name TEXT);
INSERT INTO test_log VALUES (1, 'Ayush');
Check Slot Changes
SELECT * FROM pg_logical_slot_get_changes('binlog_slot', NULL, NULL);

Expected Output:
{"change":[{"kind":"insert","table":"test_log","columnvalues":[1,"Ayush"]}]}

## 10. Start Continuous Binlog Capture

Create directory for logs:

mkdir /var/lib/pgsql/binlog
chown postgres:postgres /var/lib/pgsql/binlog

Start streaming:

pg_recvlogical -d postgres \
  --slot=binlog_slot \
  --start -f /var/lib/pgsql/binlog/pg_binlog.json

Warning:

WARNING: table "test_log" without primary key or replica identity is nothing

Fix:
ALTER TABLE test_log ADD PRIMARY KEY (id);

## 11. Generate Sample Activity
INSERT INTO test_log VALUES (100, 'Test');
UPDATE test_log SET name='Updated' WHERE id=1;
DELETE FROM test_log WHERE id=100;

## 12. Check Binlog File
cat /var/lib/pgsql/binlog/pg_binlog.json

Expected Output:
{"change":[{"kind":"insert","table":"test_log","columnvalues":[100,"Test"]}]}
{"change":[{"kind":"update","table":"test_log","columnvalues":[1,"Updated"]}]}
{"change":[{"kind":"delete","table":"test_log","columnvalues":[100]}]}

## 13. Common Issues & Fixes
Issue	Fix
File empty or not updating	Ensure pg_recvlogical is running continuously
Stopped process (^Z)	Run fg or restart command
Wrong file path	Use /var/lib/pgsql/binlog/pg_binlog.json
Peer authentication failed	Already logged in as postgres user, no su needed

## 14. Run pg_recvlogical in Background (Optional)
nohup pg_recvlogical -d postgres \
  --slot=binlog_slot \
  --start -f /var/lib/pgsql/binlog/pg_binlog.json &

